# Day 3 – API Fetcher & Library 📡

## What it does
Fetches post data from a public REST API (JSONPlaceholder)
and lets the user pick any post number (1-10) to retrieve.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3
- requests

## How to run
pip install requests
python library.py

## What I learned
- Making GET requests with requests library
- Parsing JSON responses
- Dynamic user input with API calls
- f-strings with URL building

## Output
Prints the title, body and user ID of the selected post.
